Articles.Content:
I play god and found a race of intelligent organisms called humans, who take over KSP and put their universe into a video game.

My human race.

I create my own nation and populate half of the world; I let [@TheEpicSquared](https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/158667-theepicsquared/) have the other half since I don't want to rule the *entire* world. Could you imagine the headache that must be?!

My half of a planet

I accept [@DarkOwl57](https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161624-darkowl57/)'s offer.

My half of a planet

I just open sfs file and clean away those two overlords of the Earth.  

Then reload. Just initialized noone's world.

Here I am. Here's my hill.

See it? No. That's good. Therefore, you cannot destroy it. For what you do not see you cannot destroy. Unless you shoot a .22 with your eyes closed and it ricochets off a tree, then a birdbath, and then finally your grandma's wind chime.

I edited [@kerbiloid](https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129408-kerbiloid/)'s sfs file and brought back my and [@TheEpicSquared](https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/158667-theepicsquared/)'s Empires.

Our empires

[@The Raging Sandwich](https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/164377-the-raging-sandwich/) still has a cloaked hill. I use one of my spare keys to get in, then pull out my fourth-wall-breaking equipment and lock the .sfs out for everyone else.

My hill, shared with [@The Raging Sandwich](https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/164377-the-raging-sandwich/),  [@DarkOwl57](https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161624-darkowl57/) and [@TheEpicSquared](https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/158667-theepicsquared/)'s equally divided world.

Fix mentions.

Too bad the key hole is left open. I shrink through the keyhole and take back the hill.

My hill, NOT shared with [@The Raging Sandwich](https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/164377-the-raging-sandwich/), [@DarkOwl57](https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161624-darkowl57/) and [@TheEpicSquared](https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/158667-theepicsquared/)'s equally divided world.

I take back every bit of land you took and it's now mine.

My half of a planet

Through brutal military conquest that lasted hundreds of years...
